                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13478633" author="stack" created="Thu, 18 Oct 2012 03:46:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I wonder if this issue is fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6109&quot; title=&quot;Improve RIT performances during assignment on large clusters&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6109&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6109&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  One fit criteria would be trying the assign of 1k nodes to see how long it takes when hbase-6109 is in place.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13478772" author="nkeywal" created="Thu, 18 Oct 2012 08:07:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That what my tests were saying in June. Hopefully they&apos;re right &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;. I&apos;ve not redone them recently. Hopefully it&apos;s still there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5843&quot; title=&quot;Improve HBase MTTR - Mean Time To Recover&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-5843&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-5843&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
I tested the following scenarios, on a local machine, a pseudo&lt;br/&gt;
distributed cluster with ZooKeeper and HBase writing in a ram drive,&lt;br/&gt;
no datanode nor namenode, with 2 region servers, and one empty table&lt;br/&gt;
with 10000 regions, 5K on each RS. Versions taken monday 2nd&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3) Start of the cluster after a clean stop; wait for all regions to&lt;br/&gt;
become online.&lt;br/&gt;
0.92: ~1020s&lt;br/&gt;
0.94: ~1023s (tested once only)&lt;br/&gt;
0.96: ~31s&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13479521" author="stack" created="Fri, 19 Oct 2012 00:11:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d say fit criteria for closing this issue would be running a before and after on a cluster.... see how much hbase-6109 buys us.  Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nkeywal&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nkeywal&quot;&gt;Nicolas Liochon&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13479522" author="stack" created="Fri, 19 Oct 2012 00:11:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this worth testing as part of the 0.96.0 proofing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13547632" author="stack" created="Wed, 9 Jan 2013 04:46:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nkeywal&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nkeywal&quot;&gt;Nicolas Liochon&lt;/a&gt; and/or &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jxiang&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jxiang&quot;&gt;Jimmy Xiang&lt;/a&gt; You think we can close this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13548641" author="jxiang" created="Wed, 9 Jan 2013 16:23:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I did some testing last November. We did much better than this (10+k region assigned in around 4 minutes in a 4 nodes cluster).&lt;br/&gt;
I think we can close this since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7247&quot; title=&quot;Assignment performances decreased by 50% because of regionserver.OpenRegionHandler#tickleOpening&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7247&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7247&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; could improve the performance more.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13548645" author="nkeywal" created="Wed, 9 Jan 2013 16:26:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We can, there are other jiras on this, and I don&apos;t feel rewriting the assignment today is the best thing to do. Seriously, a lot of things could be done (lowering the zk impact), but there is already something much better here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13548669" author="stack" created="Wed, 9 Jan 2013 16:45:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving as &apos;fixed&apos; though fixed elsewhere by Jimmy and Nkeywal.  Both did the necessary &apos;study&apos; and made improvements.  More to be done but enough has been done to close out this fuzzyily-described jira.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks lads.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13775471" author="stack" created="Mon, 23 Sep 2013 18:31:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking closed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
